<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 11:28AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Garvin,
southeastern Cleveland and south central McClain Counties through
NOON CDT...
At 1128 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Lindsay, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Purcell, Slaughterville, Lindsay, Lexington, Maysville, Wayne, Paoli,
Byars, Rosedale, Erin Springs and Payne.
This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 77 and 93.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
